Opening Scene

Cynthia receives and reads a letter about Alfred marrying Fionna
She burns the letter in anger, watching it fall from the window
Cynthia reflects on Hope being "too good for her" and returns to her bunk
She struggles with the collar that prevents her from speaking/screaming
She attempts to cry out "I hate you!" but cannot make sound

Confinement Period

Time passes with Cynthia refusing to participate in daily activities
She ignores the hymns, food offerings, and attempts to rouse her
The Bishop confronts Cynthia at her bedside about her behavior
They argue about the collar, religion, the Maiden, and Eleanor blasphemy
Cynthia reveals she helped birth the "prince" who is actually a girl
She discusses succession concerns - seven sonless kings, the fake male heir
The Bishop references the historical fall of Hel due to similar circumstances
He feeds her manna and encourages her to recover and learn
The Bishop reveals there's a role for her to play and promises to explain later
Sister Tyler discovers Cynthia eating and expresses surprise
Cynthia declares she'll join the nuns tomorrow but wants one day of freedom

First Day Participating

Cynthia wakes at dawn and prepares to join the daily routine
She dresses in the nun's habit and enters the chapel area
She sees Simeon across the chapel and silently curses him
Cynthia experiences the full hymn of bread, which triggers a childhood memory
She remembers secretly watching her father perform a ritual with glowing scarlet gems
After the hymn, she's emotionally overwhelmed and Sister Tyler welcomes her
Sister Tyler explains there are multiple daily hymns (bread, light, air)
Cynthia meets Glenda, another collared nun, in the dining area
They attempt conversation despite both being muted by their collars

Training Begins

Sister Tyler takes Cynthia to a study room with scrolls and a suspended gem
The nun demonstrates the hymn of light, making the gem glow
Cynthia attempts to sing but the collar mutes her completely
Sister Tyler asks Cynthia to write the words of the hymn
Cynthia writes curses instead and threatens suicide
Sister Tyler reveals she's the Bishop's wife
The nun assigns Cynthia to study the histories of Gol
Sister Tyler warns the training will take "years, not arcs"
Cynthia despairs at the lengthy sentence ahead

Time Passage (Two cycles, (8 years))

Seasons cycle through monsoon, drought, and mushroom cap growth/collapse
Cynthia matures from youth into womanhood while collared
She continues seeing Simeon wave at her during hymns

The Test

Sister Tyler summons Cynthia to meet with the Bishop
The Bishop announces they've found a suitable test for her
Four cowled men with sigils enter the room
The Bishop removes Cynthia's collar using a black rod with red crystal
The men escort Cynthia to the chapel
She discovers Anise (her former maid) collared and bound between monks
Cynthia struggles to control her rage upon seeing Anise
The Bishop removes Anise's collar so she can speak
Anise explains Lady Gestod forced her to report Cynthia's singing
Anise reveals she's married with two children and left the academy
The Bishop asks Cynthia to pass judgment on Anise
Cynthia nearly condemns her but stops to ask questions
She learns Anise was arrested for allegedly whistling at a well
The accusation came from a missing teenage boy with no written testimony
Cynthia pardons Anise and sends her home
The Bishop tests whether Cynthia's kindness is genuine
Cynthia argues about her family's reputation and demands release
The Bishop refuses, saying the situation is "gridlocked" until the Eleanor secret is revealed
He shows her a gem and musical notation documents
The Bishop confirms the stones respond to more than the three hymns
He asks her not to repeat Gol's mistake and to "find salvation"
